1.         Operating system installation and maintenance (Linux, currently Fedora)
2.         Control of user access
3.         System monitoring
4.         Management of the queuing system (SGE)
5.         Software installation and upgrade
6.         Management of databases
7.         Management and installation of the central servers and also the servers that are owned by the different research groups and the Genomics Unit
8.         Management of the backup copies of scientific data
9.         Maintenance of hardware dedicated to scientific computing
10.       Consulting for acquisition and purchases of new computing equipment
11.       Training of research staff in the good use of scientific computing equipment
12.       Coordinating with the IT department (responsible for the network administration, e-mail and windows software)
13.       Documenting all linux administrative tasks and procedures

Requirements:
The candidate should have a Computer Science/Informatics/Bioinformatics degree/equivalent with/or a demonstrated track record in:
?           Configuration and administration of Linux computer clusters
?           Knowledge of scripting languages (bash, python, perl)
?           Experience in automating OS installation
?           Strong diagnostic and analytical skills
?           Basic understanding of IT security principles and best practices
?           Experience in virtualization technology
?           Experience in monitoring and firewall systems
?           Installation and maintenance of scientific software
?           Working knowledge of Linux systems administration in a biomedical research setting and/or scientific computing and/or communications with LINUX and UNIX-based systems (including Mac OS X)
?           Fluency in English is essential.
?           Network administration skills will be considered a plus
?           Windows administration will NOT be considered.

Conditions offered:
? Full time 1 year contract, core funded, with possibility of extension
? Competitive salary according to qualifications and experience demonstrated by the candidate

